Plateau State Governorship aspirant and the leader of DVD Movement in the state, Nde Victor Dimka fsi, has suspended his political engagements and consultations till further notice following Sunday attacks at Kanam Central Senatorial Distinct that left several people dead and many others homeless. Dimka in a statement issued to newsmen in Jos said the decision was taken in view of attacks on some communities by Bandits in Kanam Local Government Area and a similar attack that took place last week in Bassa LGA, all in Plateau State where many residents were killed with several others injured. In a release signed and issued by his Media Aide, Boniface Kassam and made available to Daily Independent, said DVD leader and governorship hopeful said the suspension was to mourn with the families of the departed and condole with the Executive Governor of Plateau State, (Dr) Simon Bako Lalong, the Executive Chairmen of Kanam and Bassa Local Government Councils, and the good people of the two Local Government Areas. He described the unfortunate development as one of the most wicked and barbaric acts ever experienced on the Plateau in recent times. Nde David Victor Dimka fsi who expressed sadness also called on the government at all levels to ensure that the bandits who have been terrorizing innocent citizens, especially in some communities of the State are fished out and the law takes its course. He Recalled that the DVD Campaign Team had scheduled to visit some Local Government Areas today, Monday, April 12, 2022, but stressed that normal activities of the Movement will resume soon.